main event: An unidentified object was observed in Presque Isle, Maine on March 25, 1951, by a military source for a duration of approximately 10 minutes.
interesting points: The object was reported to be falling,The sighting was attributed to Venus due to refraction effects,The number of sightings related to this event was listed as 10,An observer in the weather office noticed a stationary light changing colors; this confirmed the visibility of the object,No photographs were taken during the sightings.
witness description: Military observer from the base weather office
